"Bopp L., Monfray P., Aumont O., Dufresne J.-L., Le Treut H., Madec G., Terray L., Orr J.C.","Potential impact of climate change on marine export production",2001,"Global Biogeochemical Cycles","15","1",,"81","99",,,10.1029/1999GB001256,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0035005046&partnerID=40&md5=b02a49dfaabe5d6820afcc1ba7b6fabd","Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire des Sciences du Climat et de l'Environnement, Gif sur Yvette, France; Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire de Météorologie Dynamique, Jussieu, Paris, France; Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire d'Océanographie Dynamique et de Climatologie, Jussieu, Paris, France; Centre Européen de Recherche et de Formation Avancée Pour le Calcul Scientifique, Toulouse, France","Bopp, L., Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire des Sciences du Climat et de l'Environnement, Gif sur Yvette, France; Monfray, P., Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire des Sciences du Climat et de l'Environnement, Gif sur Yvette, France; Aumont, O., Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire des Sciences du Climat et de l'Environnement, Gif sur Yvette, France; Dufresne, J.-L., Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire de Météorologie Dynamique, Jussieu, Paris, France; Le Treut, H., Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire de Météorologie Dynamique, Jussieu, Paris, France; Madec, G., Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire d'Océanographie Dynamique et de Climatologie, Jussieu, Paris, France; Terray, L., Centre Européen de Recherche et de Formation Avancée Pour le Calcul Scientifique, Toulouse, France; Orr, J.C., Institut Pierre-Simon Laplace, Laboratoire des Sciences du Climat et de l'Environnement, Gif sur Yvette, France","Future climate change will affect marine productivity, as well as other many components of Earth system. We have investigated the response of marine productivity to global warming with two different ocean biogeochemical schemes and two different atmosphere-ocean coupled general circulation models (GCM). Both coupled GCMs were used without flux correction to simulate climate response to increased greenhouse gases (+1% CO 2/yr for 80 years). At 2xCO 2, increased stratification leads to both reduced nutrient supply and increased light efficiency. Both effects drive a reduction in marine export production (-6%), although regionally changes can be both negative and positive (from -15% zonal average in the tropics to +10% in the Southern Ocean). Both coupled models and both biogeochemical schemes simulate a poleward shift of marine production due mainly to a longer growing season at high latitudes. At low latitudes, the effect of reduced upwelling prevails. The resulting reduction in marine productivity, and other marine resources, could become detectable in the near future, if appropriate long-term observing systems are implemented.",,"atmosphere-ocean coupling; biological production; carbon dioxide enrichment; climate change; general circulation model; marine ecosystem",,,,,,,"Bopp, L.; Inst. Pierre-Simon Laplace, Lab. Sciences Climat l'Envrn., Gif sur Yvette F-75252, France; email: bopp@lsce.saclay.cea.fr",,,,,,,,08866236,,,,"English","Global Biogeochem. Cycles",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0035005046
